Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram showing the dynamic interactions for connectivity in the eProsima FIWARE-SH system:

```plantuml
@startuml eProsima_FIWARE-SH

participant "Integration Service" as IS
participant "SystemHandle" as SH
participant "Publisher" as PUB
participant "Subscriber" as SUB
participant "NGSIV2Connector" as CONN
participant "Listener" as LIS
participant "FIWARE Context Broker" as FCB

IS -> SH : configure()
activate SH
SH -> CONN : create
activate CONN
SH -> LIS : create
activate LIS
LIS -> LIS : start_listening()

IS -> SH : register_topic()
SH -> PUB : create
activate PUB
SH -> SUB : create
activate SUB

IS -> PUB : publish(data)
PUB -> CONN : publish_to_fiware(data)
CONN -> FCB : HTTP POST (create/update entity)

FCB -> LIS : notify(data)
LIS -> CONN : on_data_received(data)
CONN -> SUB : on_subscription_data(data)
SUB -> IS : data_callback(data)

IS -> SUB : subscribe()
SUB -> CONN : subscribe_to_fiware()
CONN -> FCB : HTTP POST (create subscription)

FCB -> LIS : notify(subscribed_data)
LIS -> CONN : on_data_received(subscribed_data)
CONN -> SUB : on_subscription_data(subscribed_data)
SUB -> IS : data_callback(subscribed_data)

@enduml
```

This sequence diagram illustrates the connectivity behavior of the eProsima FIWARE-SH system, showing:

1. System initialization and configuration
2. Topic registration
3. Publishing data from Integration Service to FIWARE Context Broker
4. Receiving notifications from FIWARE Context Broker
5. Subscribing to data from FIWARE Context Broker
6. Handling incoming subscribed data

The diagram accurately represents the runtime message flow between components and services as described in the system behavior.